‚ÄúDon‚Äôt wait until it‚Äôs too late‚Äù

Unfortunately most people don‚Äôt express their gratitude towards someone until they are losing them. 

For those that follow my social media, know I preach gratitude daily and try encourage others to live a happier life. 

During these tough times I would like to try bring some positive energy across social media by asking you guys to tag 3 people that you want to know you appreciate them in your life, the more energy you give this practice the more you will take from it, maybe explain why you are so grateful for these people in your life.

...Expressing gratitude is so powerful for not only yourself but the person you express it to, touch someone with a few simple words and feel the power of gratitude.

Thank you all for this life

data.message:
Home Sweet Home...

The Cavehill, Belfast holds a special place in my heart, each time I am home it pulls me, I socialised up there most of my youth, I‚Äôve walked it with many friends and family through the years, I even dragged my Mum up one morning!

20+ years on and it still mesmerises me üíö

The crazy thing is that most from Belfast don‚Äôt appreciate it, I‚Äôve lived in a few cities around the UK and each I look to find their ‚ÄúCavehill‚Äù and there‚Äôs never one like it.

Life is full of beauty, notice it
Cx

Let‚Äôs Talk Mental Health & Music 

In recent years Northern Ireland has become a hot bed for Mental Health cases, no more so than amongst young people. Thankfully what used to be a taboo subject to talk about is changing. More and more of us are opening up to either friends or family and discussing the issues affecting our mental health.

T.A.M.H.I (Tackling Awareness of Mental Health Issues) is one local organisation tackling tie rise in cases head on. The organisation in conjunction with local ambassadors from the world of music and sport are showing those affected that there is help out there and that there are solutions and ways back from the brink.

One of those ambassadors is Northern Irish Dj, Ciaran McAuley. Ciaran is as much an active promoter of mindfulness as he is his own music and gigs. He has worked with T.A.M.H.I on a number of projects and initiatives already with the latest being the #icareandimthere .
Through this new initiative Ciaran has actively encouraged any fans or fellow musicians to reach out to him for a chat at any time about any mental health issues. A problem shared is a problem halved

T.A.M.H.I and Ciaran would like to extend an invitation to anyone of any age to come along next Thursday, 5th March at the Juice Jar in Belfast from 5pm - Late, for a discussion about mental health and music. Not only will there be an information stall on all ther help and services offered by T.A.M.H.I, there will also be a live discussion panel and a Q&A session. To round things off, Ciaran will be premiering some of his upcoming, yet to be released music and offering tips and feedback to any aspiring musicians or Djs. Ciaran will not be alone on the musical front as tunes will also be provided by local Dj and compare for the night Chris Suitor and Northern Irish Trance Family resident Djs, Ed Heaney & Symmetrik.

Big thanks has to go out to Sam and the team at The Juice Jar for hosting this inaugural event and also a big thanks to all our other partners who helped put this together.

Attendance is totally free but we do ask that you reserve your spot as space is limited

http://glist.me/icareandimthere 

Date: Thursday 5th March

Time: 5pm - late

Location: The Juice Jar,  8-10 Wellington Place, Belfast BT1 6GE

Tamhi  Audio Religion Music Northern Irish Trance Family - NITF

Our Journey...

I would like to welcome you to ‚ÄòOur Journey‚Äô:

As many of you know I fell in love with Trance music way back in the late 90s but didn‚Äôt start my solo journey in earnest until 2014. Since then I have come to realise that despite all the different countries, cities, festivals, clubs and gigs visited and played around the world, none of this would be possible if it wasn‚Äôt for all the love and support of so many like minded people, and I soon came to realise, it‚Äôs not ‚Äòmy‚Äô journey it‚Äôs ‚Äòour‚Äô journey!

Following the huge success of my debut in San Francisco last year, it‚Äôs an absolute pleasure to be invited back for my very first O2C and an honour to be asked to produce the 10 year‚Äôs of Trance Families anthem.

This dream is my oxygen and you guys fuel it.

See you all March 27th

Cx

*COMPETITION TIME*

I thought I would try something different with this competition, maybe it will encourage more positive energy out there and bring happiness to some during this festive period.

Take a few minutes, get away from the noise and tell me 3 things you are grateful for, the more you switch off and truly feel it, the more you will benefit from this practice. 

Things to be grateful for could be the likes of your health, the food on your table, your loved ones around you, the warm home you live in, your job...

Gratitude is one of the most powerful emotions and sadly only few practice it, we all have so much to be grateful for but most focus on the things we don‚Äôt have.

Remember, what we feed grows, so if it‚Äôs gratitude you feed then it‚Äôs gratitude that grows.

1. List 3 things you are grateful for
2. Share this post
3. Have a great Christmas 

2 Winners will be selected at random and each will receive a Ciaran McAuley shirt and 2 wristbands each plus a signed copy of the FSOE600 album mixed by myself and trance icons Aly&Fila. 

Best of luck
Cx

Future Sound of Egypt Aly & Fila

FOOD FOR THOUGHT

* What You Feed Grows 

This is something I preach often and can‚Äôt express enough. Remember our feelings only come from our thoughts, once I learnt this I became very careful as to what I let in. 

What are your habits, especially in the morning, are they fuelling you or deteriorating you? 

* Life Leaves Patterns

Think of all the times you felt good or motivated, what were you doing then? 

Also, you can learn a lot from others around you. If you know someone who is negative or unhappy all the time, you know not to follow their habits.

Try be more self aware, spend more time on you and look after your well-being

Hope this helps some out there
Cx

Tamhi
